{"word":"σωματικός","slug":"σωματικός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>σωματικός</b></el> <el>(σωμᾰτικός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:σῶμα'><el>σῶμα</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>of</i> or <i>for the body, bodily</i>, <a href='S:Latin'>Lat.</a> <el>corporeus</el>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-κῶς</el>, <b><a href='S:New Testament'>NTest.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>bodily, corporeal, material</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristotle'>Arist.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}